FBIS4-58297 "drnes085_c_94015" FBIS-NES-94-085 Daily Report 30 Apr 1994 Egypt Correspondent Sentenced to 1 Year Imprisonment Correspondent Sentenced to 1 Year Imprisonment NC0105062494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2035 GMT 30 Apr 94 NC0105062494 Cairo MENA Arabic BFN [Text] Cairo, 30 Apr (MENA)--A military court has sentenced 'Abd-al-Sattar Abu-Husayn, a journalist for AL-SHA'B, mouthpiece of the opposition Labor Party, to one year in prison and fined him 500 pounds for publishing news related to the Armed Forces without prior permission. The journalist can appeal for commutation or cancellation of the sentence or for a retrial. If the ruling is confirmed, a petition for a reconsideration of the sentence can be made to the military appeals office within 15 days from the date the convict is notified of the confirmation.
